element.name: Scores
element.documentation:
Columns:
- Object_ID: UID of the scored object (party, product, transaction, ...) - Snapshot_date: Date for which the score is relevant - View_ID: ID of the View used. Needed to determine the object aggration level. - View_aggregation_level: Client, Product, Household, ... - Model_ID: ID of the model that has been used to produce the score. - Model_name: name of the model used for scoring. - Model_version: version of the model used for scoring. - Score: normalized value between 0-100, essentially a percentile. - Score_bucket: score bucketing, if applicable. - Score_bucketing_scheme_ID - Probability: between 0 - 1. Probability of event happening (e.g. probability of default, ...) - Probability_bucket: probability bucketing, if applicable. - Probability_bucketing_scheme_ID - Creation_date: Date at which the score has been calculated
